        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 7:55PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 755 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Leasburg, or 9 miles west of Roxboro, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Roxboro, Concord, Bethel Hill, Bushy Fork, Hyco Lake, Mayo Reservoir,
and Hyco Marina.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
